node.text: Had to add the Jin Chan to the #DynastyCollection & add a twist w/ a centenario coin in his mouth… everything #DoneRight baby @donerightandco - The Jin Chan (aka Money toad or Money Frog) is usually depicted as a bullfrog with red eyes, flared nostrils and only one hind leg (for a total of three legs), sitting on a pile of traditional Chinese cash, with a coin in its mouth. On its back, it often displays seven diamond spots. According to Feng Shui beliefs, Jin Chan helps attract and protect wealth, and guards against bad luck…

node.text: Words can’t explain the feeling to be honored by the city council, Congress woman @repjacksonlee & the mayor @sylvesterturner It was an eventful night & I’m just blessed to be in a room with such good people. Where I come from we don’t get awards for stuff we do from the heart so I was in disbelief when I got the call from the dennis’s. It was amazing hearing everyone else’s stories, shout out to the other honorees. I’ll continue to keep doing what I do & pushing boundaries to show the streets that we can overcome & change our situation as long as we want to bad enough. Just cause we made bad choices doesn’t mean we’re bad people. I was once labeled a menace to society & now I’m considered a Philanthropist & a Pilar to the community… God is GREAT!!! Thank you again #Houston #L2H #Live2Help #IAmAStreetDream #HoustonHumanitarianOfTheYear #HumanitarianOfTheYear #MadeInAlief
